                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="1r" to="78v" facs="0003"/>
                        <seg type="script">15th-century script</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1499">15th century</date>
                        <desc>
                           Some paleographic features:
                           the upper part of some letters, e.g. ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ, and ዐ has a triangular shape;
                           ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line;
                           the right stroke of ለ is slightly slanted to the left;
                           numerals are written without dashes;
                           ፪ has angular and not separated loops;
                           ፮ has the loop open, looking like "compressed" ፯;
                           ፴ has no left stroke;
                           the zǝya-sign (ligature of ዝ and የ) is written on the right margin of the leaf;
                           cruces ansatae are written in black ink on the right margin of the leaf every ten Psalms.
                        </desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Numbers and titles of the Psalms.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="79r" to="118v" facs="0081"/>
                        <seg type="script">15th-century script</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1499">15th century</date>
                        <desc>
                           Some paleographic features:
